attributeList.attribute: The core enzyme of PP2A comprises a catalytic subunit, the C-subunit (PP2Ac), and a scaffolding protein, the A subunit. The substrate specificity of PP2A as well as its intracellular localization are defined by an array of distinct groups of B-type regulatory subunits that bind to the AC dimeric core to form a variety of heterotrimeric complexes.

A serine/threonine protein phosphatase complex that plays a major role in TOR1/2 (P35169/P32600)-mediated signaling and gene expression. Rapamycin causes release of the phosphatase-RRD dimer from TAP42.
